node.text: Such a rad time with an awesome group of peoples. The @GridExperience definitely sets the bar (and sets it pretty high) for me when it comes to indoor karting. Combine that with a this crew of friends and fam: Jeremy McGrath, Sage Kotsenburg, Zak Hale, Davey Coombs (founder of Racer X), Zac Mertens (of Hoonigan Racing), etc. - plus Jett and Hunter Lawrence were two of the top three fastest of the night (same positions as they finished in the 250 Main of the Supercross race this past weekend!). Jeremy’s daughter (Rhowan) and my daughter (Lia) both had two of the top lap five times also (yep, we’re proud Dads!). Good times!

node.title: Rad time karting at The Grid Experience with friends and fam.

node.text: The @GridExperience’s indoor kart track is really amazing. It’s a half mile long, 3-level, has two banked corners, a drop - and the electric karts have a boost button! node.text: This weekend will be my first competitive drive in a Subaru since 2009. With only one proper day of testing before @AlexGelsomino and I show up this weekend to the @OlympusRally (3rd round of the @ARA_Rally Championship) it will be interesting to see how quickly I can get fully comfortable in it and run at full tilt. But so far, the car looks (livery by @ItsALiving) and feels (built and prepped by Vermont SportsCar) great! Check out this week's episode on my YouTube channel (link in bio) for the livery reveal, and to hear about all our plans for a wild year! #gravelslayingaction

node.text: Here’s another AINT CARE moment from the vault: @AlexGelsomino and I lost our front right side wheel midway through Stage 3 (of Oregon Trail Rally in 2013) due to a freak mechanical failure. We kept the hammer down and finished that stage, and then continued on to run another full stage on just 3 wheels, rather than settling for a DNF. We finished the race 2nd overall - all because we were able to drive through this #AINTCARE situation!

node.text: AIN’T CARE, rally cross example: after qualifying first, winning each of the heats, and leading the first 5 laps of the Final in the 2012 GRC race in Las Vegas, the ECU/control panel in my race car caught fire. I continued the race for as long as I could, but the fumes from the fire were starting to burn my lungs. I led and raced for as long as I could but eventually had to stop. I truly tried to AIN’T CARE as long as I could, but wasn’t willing to die for the win. 🤷‍♂️ #AINTCARE #pressonregardless

node.text: Lots of rain prior to The Rally in the 100 Acre Wood this year made for some very wet and rough stretches of the race stages. This video from Stage 12 is a sample of that at this year’s race in Salem, Missouri. @AlexGelsomino and I were fastest on this stage during the race, helping us secure 2nd place overall. Click the link to see the full on-board video from the entire 10.84 mile stage. #100AW

node.text: BIG congrats on the podium finishes of my buddies Dustin Jones and Donald “Cowboy” Cerrone (yes, the legendary UFC fighter) in the Vegas To Reno race! Both were racing Can-Am Maverick X3’s, but in different classes: Dustin earned 2nd in "Pro Turbo” class and Cowboy got 3rd in “UTV Rally” class. Rad. #CanAmMaverickX3 #VegasToReno

node.text: Getting more confident riding my moto bike. I have ridden dirt bikes (mostly on tracks) since I was 12, but didn’t ride for 15 years because I was racing rally (a bit scared of getting hurt and not being able to race). But now, I am back at it - and it’s a dream come true having an epic track in my backyard! Great shots by: @garthmilan. #motokidforlife

node.text: 350 miles - the longest rally-type stage Alex & I have ever done!! Jax and Bryan did another 140 miles, for a total of 490 for the whole race. We lost the hood, rear fender, one side of the Borla exhaust, power steering was struggling for the last half of the race, intercom was having issues, many flats, and our hydraulic jacks stopped working after a few of the flats. But, we finished!! And finished (with all those issues) in 10th place (out of 30 trucks). Amazing experience and great preparation for the Baja 1000. Big thanks to the whole team for all the hard work and effort! #WhoopocalypseNow #TrophyTruck #VegasToReno

node.text: 3rd in qualifying, and running in the top 5 overall by mile 100 - the initial part of my offroad race world debut went very well (I even passed my friend BJ Baldwin)!! But then, my run in “Vegas to Reno” started to fall apart. Literally. Alex Gelsomino and I started getting an unusual amount of flats (from what I’m told) in our 350 mile stint and the trend continued when Jax Redline and his co-driver Bryan Hansen got in. So, it was too many for a chance at the podium spot, especially when we had a power steering issue develop late in the race. We finished 10th, but this race was all about seat time and experience so I feel it was a good outing for my first Trophy Truck race! And, this was great preparation for the Baja 1000, so I am happy about that. Photos by: @highrevphoto #VegasToReno #TrophyTruck #WhoopocalypseNow

To see the full stage and hear more about it and this difficult rally, click the link in my bio. #NEFR

node.text: BIG thanks to all you fans who voted on the graphic options for my new @iamspecialized Turbo Kenevo SL! This is the graphic scheme that won: my 2021 Hoonigan Racing livery art (same graphics on my rally cars and Trophy Truck) by “It’s A Living”. We had some other great options that I really liked (like the Drips livery from Gymkhana THREE), but this one was def my favorite, so I am stoked that you all liked it too. #iamspecialized #SpecializedTurboKenovoSL

node.text: Jumps, jumps, and more jumps. Most of them in 6th gear! The Concord Pond stage of the New England Forest Rally is one of my favorite stages in the entire world. Why? Well… jumps! Ha. See the full stage from my view (helmet cam) in the new episode on my YouTube channel, via the link in bio. #airtimeisagoodtime #NEFR

node.text: Raw onboard video time! Concord Pond is one of, if not the gnarliest rally stage, in the American Rally Association championship. It’s a high speed rollercoaster: lots of jumps, turns over crests, flat-out 6th gear sections, etc. It’s very similar to the WRC Finland stages. Check out the latest episode on my YouTube channel (link in bio) to see the full helmet cam run. #NEFR
